{"id":14881611,"mediaExerciseId":"6a95e267-12f2-4c8f-9e5e-9fe17d31be7e","exerciseName":"13","chapterName":"17","chapterTitle":"Dividends and Payout Policy","groupId":612429,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":604,"solutions":[{"id":6001122,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are required to determine the pre-tax required return on Gordon's stock. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/81c5e564df99727493434f0e3a139b65/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/81c5e564df99727493434f0e3a139b65/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Required rate of return** is the minimal profit (return) that an investor must receive in exchange for accepting the risk of investing a stock or other type of security investment.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/a4012a19bbdec6348c14da9a40e6ccb8/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/a4012a19bbdec6348c14da9a40e6ccb8/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's identify the given amounts in the problem.\n\n| |Amounts | \n|--|--:| \n| Gordon's Dividend Yield| 2.9%| \n| Income Tax Rate|35% | \n| Gecko's expected earnings growth rate| 12\\%| \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/3599422a04045cf0ef68e6b8e94cc7a4/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/3599422a04045cf0ef68e6b8e94cc7a4/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"To begin, let's compute the earnings growth rate. Note that the after-tax expected return on the two stocks are equal.\n\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{EGR} &= \\text{After-Tax Required Return} - [\\text{DY}\\times (1 - r)]\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\nEGR - Earnings Growth Rate\n\nDY - Dividend Yield\n\nr - Tax Rate\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":304,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/9297635da6ca655d5d57f2721abd0c2c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":154,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/9297635da6ca655d5d57f2721abd0c2c/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, we can compute the earnings growth rate of Gordon using the equation in step 4.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{EGR} &= \\text{After-Tax Required Return} - [\\text{DY}\\times (1 - r)]\\\\[5pt]\n &= \\text{12\\%} - [\\text{2.9\\%}\\times {\\text(1 - 35\\%)}]\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{12\\%} - [\\text{2.9\\%}\\times {\\text(0.65)}]\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{12\\%} - {\\text(0.0189)}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\text{10.1\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nAs can be seen, the earnings growth rate of Gordon is 10.1%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Lastly, now that we have computed the earnings growth rate of Gordon, we can now compute the pre-tax by adding the earnings growth rate by the dividend yield.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Pre -tax Required Return} &= \\text{EGR} + {\\text{DY}}\\\\[5pt]\n &= \\text{10.1\\%} + {\\text{2.9\\%}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{13\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTherefore, the pre-tax required return on Gordon's stock is **13\\%**.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":353,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/00107b1778479dbaf4a9e87ba67deaf1/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":178,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/41bfdf8130e712b4ac2b2706ee5f0fd1/00107b1778479dbaf4a9e87ba67deaf1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"44281271-84ee-423e-83af-f665bc9f44fa","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881612,"exerciseName":"14","page":604,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ef630188-c744-4b2a-933f-6e109ca543f6","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-14-ef630188-c744-4b2a-933f-6e109ca543f6"},{"id":14881613,"exerciseName":"15","page":604,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"95e29f4b-88a5-4ac5-b729-94a9611ce6d9","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fu